    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "DELAND, Fla. \u2013\nNorth Florida Baseball earned a series win to open ASUN Conference play when it defeated Stetson, 4-1, at Conrad Park on Sunday.\nThe Ospreys recorded 19 hits over the final two games to take the series.\nStetson scored its lone run in the bottom of the first inning. The Hatters registered three of its five hits in the frame.\u00a0North Florida responded with a three-run fifth inning to secure the lead. Redshirt freshman outfielder\nSean Benjamin\nopened the inning with a leadoff double before senior catcher\nSantiago Ordonez\ndrew a walk to put runners on first and second with no outs. Benjamin has posted a team-high eight doubles this season.\nNorth Florida then loaded the bases on a Stetson error and junior infielder\nMitchell Collins\ndrew a bases-loaded walk to put the Ospreys on the board. Junior infielder\nMathew Farner\ndrove in a pair of runs with a single to center field to give the Ospreys a 3-1 lead in the fifth inning.\nSenior right-handed pitcher\nBrandon Adams\nturned in three no-hit innings of relief with four strikeouts to earn his first win of the season. Freshman right-handed pitcher\nDevin Diggs\nclosed out the final two innings to add his first save of the season.\nNorth Florida added its fourth run on a wild pitch in the ninth inning to secure the eventual final.\nNORTH FLORIDA 4, STETSON 1\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nBrandon Adams\n(1-0)\nLoss: Trace Hartman (2-2)\nSave:\nDevin Diggs\n(1)\nLine Scores\nNORTH FLORIDA | 4 R, 5 H, 1 E, 7 LOB\nSTETSON | 1 R, 5 H, 3 E, 7 LOB\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nMathew Farner\n| 2-4, 2 RBI\nSantiago Ordonez\n| 1-3, R, 2B, BB\nBrandon Adams\n| 3.0 IP, 4K, 0 H, 0 ER\nSTETSON\nYohann Dessureault | 1-3, RBI\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida travels to Charleston, S.C. to rematch with Charleston Southern at CSU Ballpark on Tuesday, March 17 at 6 p.m. ET."
